<DOC><DOCNO> AP881229-0033 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-12-29-88 0217EST</FILEID><FIRST>r w PM-BailoutsList     12-29 0208</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Bailouts List,210</SECOND><HEAD>With PM-Sandamp;L Bailouts Bjt</HEAD><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Here is a list of the biggest governmentbailout packages to date in terms of estimated costs to the FederalHome Loan Bank Board and its insurance arm, the Federal Savings andLoan Insurance Corp:   1. $5.5 billion in government assistance pledged on Aug. 19 tomerge eight insolvent Texas savings and loans into a new institutioncalled Sunbelt Savings F.S.B.   2. $5.1 billion pledged on Wednesday to merge five insolventTexas Sandamp;Ls into a new institution called First Texas Bank F.S.B.   3. $2 billion pledged on May 18 for four insolvent Texasinstitutions to be acquired by Southwest Savings Association ofDallas.   4. $1.85 billion pledged on Dec. 22 to merge 15 failed Texas Sandamp;Lsinto a new institution called Consolidated Federal Bank, run byJames Fail of Phoenix, the chairman of several insurance companies.   5. $1.7 billion pledged on Wednesday for American Savings ofStockton, Calif., the largest single insolvent Sandamp;L, to be acquiredby a group headed by Texas billionaire Robert M. Bass.   6. $1.3 billion pledged on Aug. 18 for Gibson Group-LSSTFinancial Services, headed by a Chicago banker and backed by a Texassteel company, to acquire 12 insolvent Texas savings institutions.</TEXT></DOC>